cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

This paper deals with improving the generalization performance of a fingerprint spoof detector, which involves image processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with security and privacy issues related to biometric authentication, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper proposes a new approach to improve the generalization performance of a state-of-the-art spoof detector, which involves training a CNN to learn generative-noise invariant features, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with large-scale datasets and cross-sensor spoof detection, which falls under the categories of cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), respectively.
